Jamovi - Introduction

Problem 1

In this section, you will learn how to check your jamovi version.

Let’s try to answer the question, which jamovi version am I running, is there a newer one?

  1. Open the jamovi statistical software (If it is not installed on your computer, you can do this from https://jamovi.org).
  1. Check the version number of jamovi running on your computer. There are two methods. The current version number is available from the home screen.

Also, by clicking on the 3 dots in the upper right corner, you can also see the version number at the bottom of the window that appears.

  1. Compare the version number of jamovi running on your computer to the latest version available from https://jamovi.org.

As you can see, we are using the latest version of jamovi. We have nothing to do, jamovi is up-to-date. We check the jamovi site every two to three months to see if a new version of jamovi is available.

Problem 2

In this section, you will learn how to navigate in jamovi.

The user interface of jamovi is structured extremely logically. It is important to be aware of how we can access the 3 panels:

  • Data panel: In a jamovi program instance, we can always analyse only one dataset. This dataset is what ‘Data panel’ contains.
  • Analysis panel: We can initiate any number of analyses from the menu Analayses. We always see the current analysis in the ‘Analysis panel’.
  • Results panel: Each analysis has a separate results section. The results of all analyses performed in the jamov instance are available in the ‘Results panel’. By clicking on a result section, the corresponding analysis section will be loaded into the ‘Analysis panel’.

  1. Open the jamovi statistical software.

  2. Identify the panels that appear. After starting, only the ‘Data panel’ is visible.

  1. Select the menu Exploration / Descriptive and identify the panels that appear. Two bars are separating the three panels, and these can be dragged to the left or the right to change their sizes.
  1. Hide the ‘Analyses panel’. Click on the arrow in the upper right corner of the ‘Analyses panel’.
  1. Show the ‘Analyses panel’. Click on Descriptive part of the ‘Result pane’.
  1. Hide the ‘Data panel’. Click on the small icon in the upper right corner of the jamovi.
  1. Show the ‘Data panel’. Click on the small icon in the upper right corner of the jamovi.
  1. Create another analysis using Analyses / T-Test / One Sample T-test. Note that a new analysis section has been added to the ‘Result panel’. The ‘Result panel’ now contains two analysis sections.
  1. Let’s make available the ‘Analyzes panel’ belonging to the first analysis section (Descriptive statistics). Click on Descriptive part of ‘Result panel’
